{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Deu|14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","chapter":14,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":1,"text":"“You are sons of the Lord your God; do not cut yourselves or make a bald spot on your head on behalf of the dead,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":2,"text":"for you are a holy people belonging to the Lord your God. The Lord has chosen you to be his own possession out of all the peoples on the face of the earth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":3,"text":"“You must not eat any detestable thing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":4,"text":"These are the animals you may eat:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":5,"text":"deer, gazelles, roe deer,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":6,"text":"You may eat any animal that has hooves divided in two and chews the cud.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":7,"text":"But among the ones that chew the cud or have divided hooves, you are not to eat these:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":8,"text":"and pigs, though they have hooves, they do not chew the cud —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":9,"text":"“You may eat everything from the water that has fins and scales,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":10,"text":"but you may not eat anything that does not have fins and scales —it is unclean for you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":11,"text":"“You may eat every clean bird,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":12,"text":"but these are the ones you may not eat:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":13,"text":"the kites,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":14,"text":"every kind of raven,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":15,"text":"ostriches,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":16,"text":"little owls, long-eared owls,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":17,"text":"eagle owls,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":18,"text":"storks,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":19,"text":"All winged insects are unclean for you; they may not be eaten.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":20,"text":"But you may eat every clean flying creature.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":21,"text":"“You are not to eat any carcass; you may give it to a resident alien within your city gates, and he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner. For you are a holy people belonging to the Lord your God. Do not boil a young goat in its mother’s milk.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":22,"text":"“Each year you are to set aside a tenth of all the produce grown in your fields.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":23,"text":"You are to eat a tenth of your grain, new wine, and fresh oil, and the firstborn of your herd and flock, in the presence of the Lord your God at the place where he chooses to have his name dwell, so that you will always learn to fear the Lord your God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":24,"text":"But if the distance is too great for you to carry it, since the place where the Lord your God chooses to put his name is too far away from you and since the Lord your God has blessed you,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":25,"text":"then exchange it for silver, take the silver in your hand, and go to the place the Lord your God chooses.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":26,"text":"You may spend the silver on anything you want: cattle, sheep, goats, wine, beer, or anything you desire. You are to feast there in the presence of the Lord your God and rejoice with your family.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":27,"text":"Do not neglect the Levite within your city gates, since he has no portion or inheritance among you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":28,"text":"“At the end of every three years, bring a tenth of all your produce for that year and store it within your city gates.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","bookOrder":4,"chapter":14,"verse":29,"text":"Then the Levite, who has no portion or inheritance among you, the resident alien, the fatherless, and the widow within your city gates may come, eat, and be satisfied. And the Lord your God will bless you in all the work of your hands that you do.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Deu","chapter":14,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,5,6,8,9,11,13,14,16,17,18,19,21,22,28],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Forbidden Practices"},{"beforeVerse":3,"text":"Clean and Unclean Foods"},{"beforeVerse":22,"text":"A Tenth for the Lord"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“You are sons of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 4:22–23","book":"Exo","chapter":4,"verse":22,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 32:6","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" do not cut yourselves or make a bald spot on your head "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or forehead"},{"kind":"text","text":" on behalf of the dead, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 19:28","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":28,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 4:22–23","book":"Exo","chapter":4,"verse":22},{"label":"Dt 32:6","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":6},{"label":"Lv 19:28","book":"Lev","chapter":19,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or forehead"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"for you are a holy people belonging to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God. The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has chosen you to be his own possession "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 19:5","book":"Exo","chapter":19,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 7:6","book":"Deu","chapter":7,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" out of all the peoples on the face of the earth."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 19:5","book":"Exo","chapter":19,"verse":5},{"label":"Dt 7:6","book":"Deu","chapter":7,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“You must not eat any detestable thing. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"These are the animals you may eat:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"deer, gazelles, roe deer,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You may eat any animal that has hooves divided in two and chews the cud. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"The Hb does not specify chewing the cud, but bringing up partially digested food and swallowing it again."},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"The Hb does not specify chewing the cud, but bringing up partially digested food and swallowing it again."}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But among the ones that chew the cud or have divided hooves, you are not to eat these:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and pigs, though they have hooves, they do not chew the cud —"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“You may eat everything from the water that has fins and scales, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"but you may not eat anything that does not have fins and scales —it is unclean for you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 11:9","book":"Lev","chapter":11,"verse":9,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lv 11:9","book":"Lev","chapter":11,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“You may eat every clean bird, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"but these are the ones you may not eat:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"the kites,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"every kind of raven, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"ostriches,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"little owls, long-eared owls,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"eagle owls,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"storks,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"All winged insects are unclean for you; they may not be eaten. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But you may eat every clean flying creature. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lv 11:20","book":"Lev","chapter":11,"verse":20,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lv 11:20","book":"Lev","chapter":11,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“You are not to eat any carcass; you may give it to a resident alien within your city gates, and he may eat it, or you may sell it to a foreigner. For you are a holy people belonging to the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God. Do not boil a young goat in its mother’s milk."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Each year you are to set aside a tenth of all the produce grown in your fields. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You are to eat a tenth of your grain, new wine, and fresh oil, and the firstborn of your herd and flock, in the presence of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God at the place where he chooses to have his name dwell, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:11","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that you will always learn to fear "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 4:10","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 6:2","book":"Deu","chapter":6,"verse":2,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 10:12","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":12,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 17:19","book":"Deu","chapter":17,"verse":19,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 31:12–13","book":"Deu","chapter":31,"verse":12,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 4:24","book":"Jos","chapter":4,"verse":24,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 24:14","book":"Jos","chapter":24,"verse":14,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 12:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":14,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:25","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":25,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 15:4","book":"Psa","chapter":15,"verse":4,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"text","text":" the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 12:11","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":11},{"label":"Dt 4:10","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":10},{"label":"Dt 6:2","book":"Deu","chapter":6,"verse":2},{"label":"Dt 10:12","book":"Deu","chapter":10,"verse":12},{"label":"Dt 17:19","book":"Deu","chapter":17,"verse":19},{"label":"Dt 31:12–13","book":"Deu","chapter":31,"verse":12},{"label":"Jos 4:24","book":"Jos","chapter":4,"verse":24},{"label":"Jos 24:14","book":"Jos","chapter":24,"verse":14},{"label":"1Sm 12:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":14},{"label":"2Kg 17:25","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":25},{"label":"Ps 15:4","book":"Psa","chapter":15,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But if the distance is too great for you to carry it, since the place where the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God chooses to put his name is too far away from you and since the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God has blessed you, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"then exchange it for silver, take the silver in your hand, and go to the place the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God chooses. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You may spend the silver on anything you want: cattle, sheep, goats, wine, beer, or anything you desire. You are to feast there in the presence of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God and rejoice with your family. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Do not neglect the Levite within your city gates, since he has no portion or inheritance among you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:12","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:18","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":18,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 12:12","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":12},{"label":"Dt 12:18","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“At the end of every three years, bring a tenth of all your produce for that year and store it within your city gates. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Deu:14:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then the Levite, who has no portion or inheritance among you, the resident alien, the fatherless, and the widow within your city gates may come, eat, and be satisfied. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 26:12","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" And the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" your God will bless you in all the work of your hands that you do. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 30:9","book":"Deu","chapter":30,"verse":9,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 26:12","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":12},{"label":"Dt 30:9","book":"Deu","chapter":30,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099263062}